caption: Yummy comfort Thai food. I’ve been going here since I was a freshman at DePaul and have been getting food from there at least once a month for the past 9 years. Solid go-to location
get the orange chicken with fried rice and hot sauce, best combo ever. Def worth the money.
Their always friendly and the food is always fresh and delicious.
Very good attention! So nice, everything was delicious. The lumpia were perfect size, chicken pad thai amazing and the mango sticky rice was TO DIE FOR!!!! Best one I’ve had.
Quality Thai food
I love this place, especially their panang curry. They're the only Thai place near me that actually gives you the option to select how spicy you want it, and will actually make it spicy!
Worse food I ever had. I got sick from it. Will never go there again.

Based on friendliness of staff - 5 stars, they were so sweet and happy. However there seemed to be a language barrier, as one of the people in our party ordered the broccoli and carrot with vegetables, and asked what sauce it was stir fried in, as she is gluten free.  He then served her a small plate of steamed broccoli - definitely not worth the $10 she was charged. Another in our party asked for Thai level spiciness but said his dish didn’t deliver. As for my dish, it was reminiscent of making instant ramen but draining most of the water. Flavorful, but in a flavor packet kind of way. Service itself was very slow, we weren’t really checked on after we got our food, and it took a while to get anyone’s attention even though it was clear we had been done with our meal for a while.

The food here is amazing. Secret “hole in the wall.” I order take out every other week. Yes, add the hot sauce! Delish.  Update - when I stopped by one time for my take out the owner/hostess sliced a rambutan and insisted I try. Yum! Such a kind gesture.

I lived next door to this spot for a few months and can’t lie, I ordered take out once or twice a week. It’s a cute little family run restaurant, and it’s authentic***. The woman who runs the spot knew my order and would always make sure my Thai Iced Coffee was mixed just right (she let me do it myself even) before I left, every time. I honestly loved visiting them every week and I miss it incredibly so now that I moved!
The Food is amazing and totally worth going for. But you might be lucky enough to grab a palm read from Miss Asia

I was walking and found this little piece of heaven, the place lovely, food fabulous, service was sooo friendly. I feel in love with the owner, such a beautiful soul and spirited woman. Take a group of friends/ family for an Asian delightful experience.👍😋

You must try this place! The food is beyond delicious, but the staff are really what made our meal enjoyable! Our waitress suggested we get the sticky rice and mango for dessert, but it was more of a command than a suggestion because she wouldn’t take no for an answer. Haha. She knew what she was talking about. — it was SOO GOOOOD!  We were the last customers of the night and before she would charge our bill she insisted on reading our palms. We could tell that she really knew her stuff and appreciated her knowledge. The entire walk home we all talked about the different things she had seen on our palms and how fun the evening had been.  We will be going back!!
Loved it
Quaint, great food and amazing service! If you are in Chicago, make sure you stop by.
I have been to many Thai restaurants and Miss Asia is the best.
Lovely family run restaurant that may shut down soon as owner is retiring. Authentic Thai ...delicious food and very reasonable. They have an awesome three course lunch menu for 9 bucks
Good food. Heed the spice warnings
Wow
$9 lunch special every day of the week where you have plenty of choices to choose from. The pad thai was pretty typical of what you'd find elsewhere in the city.
Good lunch specials...decent food and nice service. Overall, a good value and worth the visit.
Staff was friendly and attentive. Carry out was ready on time and was fresh as if dining in. Would recommend!
delicious
The food was delicious, the service was friendly, and the place is BYOB. I highly recommend if you are in to Thai/Chinese dishes.
Really great fried tofu. Tastes like chicken nuggets!

Great place for inexpensive Thai/Chinese food. They have a lunch specials menu that is very popular.  The service is very quick (and they deliver too). Not the most attentive staff but pleasant nonetheless.

Chose this place based on reviews about the quality authentic food, and the lunch special. This was for sure the worst Thai food I have ever had. $9 for the special isn’t a bargain here. I’ve had Lunch specials for $7.95 in the city. Regardless of the price, the food had no flavor. I ordered the red curry with tofu. The curry sauce was scant and so watered down I couldn’t taste anything other than a little heat. For the first time in my life, I was going to ask for salt at a Thai restaurant. I realized nothing was gonna say that dish.  Tom Yum soup had zero heat, no lemongrass flavor, and the only thing that was good was the crab Rangoon,  but how can you go wrong with that. I would give it one star...in fact I don’t even know I’m giving it two.
I love when the elder Asian woman is there she is nice, friendly and helpful. The food is tasty as well, this is the only place I go to have thai style food
Tasty food and priced right. Would revisit.
Food is not exemplary but not bad if you want a quite place that has food late at night you can do worse.
The week day lunch special is remarkably affordable for the top quality Thai food. Thr tam yum soup with chicken was very memorable. Everything was good.
Hospitality is above and beyond! Food is superb!
Owner is rude, food is subpar
This food is amazing!!! Had the larb kai, papaya salad, cucumber salad, green curry with tofu, and pad Thai chicken. Honestly this is some of the best Thai food in Chicago! Don’t miss this treat!
You can taste how fresh the ingredients are. My favorite is the red curry chicken, max spicy.  Awesome!!
Food--which matters the most--was superb
(Translated by Google) Bad service  (Original) Mal servicio
I love this restaurant.  Food is excellent.  The staff is friendly and helpful.  They  will prepare your food your way.

After taking a horrible lunch at a Thailand restaurant in Houston today , I am missing this restaurant in Chicago so so so much … If you want to try the authentic Thai food, do tell the lady that you want a home style cooking! The owner modified the recipe so that their food can be accepted by most American people. However, the modified Thai cuisines is too sweet to enjoy the real Thai favor! Don’t miss the “Tiger cry”, green curry and a dish made by fried catfish! If you don’t know what to order, feel free to ask a recommendation.
Great food and awesome waitress!!!!
Service a little slow, but the food was amazing!
Great Thai lunch. Really enjoyed it!
Very dumpy portions. Not cool.
This is a nice place in the neighborhood to go for Asian Cuisine. The BYOB is a nice feature. The lunch special is a pretty good deal
Ok.. service not real good

Their Tom Kha soup is beyond fabulous! Best news of all, it can be part of their lunch special (appetizer, soup, entree all for $7.95). I go medium on the soup's spiciness and request veggies only, no chicken. Seriously good.
Very nice Thai cuisine. The staff was great and courteous. Food was excellent and authentic.
One of the best lunch specials in the city. Their panang curry is my favorite!

Amazing food. We have a Thai friend with us so we know it's absolutely good and classic.  Also the waitresses is a legendary: speaks 3 languages and knows how to read fate by looking at your palms (decent accuracy as she even reveals my never told secrets).  EDIT: That "waitresses" is actually the owner. She just enjoys work at the frontline directly.
A bit pricey, but that's the location. Great food.
delicious Thai food
Very tasty and prices are reasonable
Best east lakeview thai place. The staff are friendly and service is very fast. Food is always amazing. Don't miss the Mango sticky rice!
Well priced delicious Thai food :)
The soup and appetizer were good but the Kung Pao chicken was pretty bad. It had no flavor and was soupy and watery
Fantastic value and good is amazing! Love the Panang curry!
Delicious family restaurant with speedy delivery, this is definitely my go to Thai restaurant.
Great food at OK prices.
Surprisingly tasty for the price. Service was good and friendly. Would definitely come back if in the area.
I ordered the pad Thai and it had no flavor. it didn't taste anything like how pad Thai should taste.
Food is good but not great if compare with other thai restaurant.
Great food, plenty of tables, friendly staff, what's not to like?

Nice food, good prices, cozy place. Respect
Authentic Thai food

MIss Asia was a great find in the Lakeview area. They have an extensive menu of Thai and Chinese cuisines and almost everything I've tried has been delicious. Try the bangcock chicken, but choose carefully when they ask how spicy you want it. They're also open until 3-4am every night and it's BYOB. Can't beat that.
good food but they never want to take m y coupons...what gives?

I order from Miss Asia at least twice a week. The Crag Rangoon is always great! (i mean who doesn't like Crab Rangoon!) But i always try to change up my order between their great noodle dishes from the Pad Thai to the Pad See Ewe.... always great and i always ask for it to be spicy... i like the spice.. overall Miss Asia is a great asian place to order in from.
Cheap thai food, quick service overall very decent place!
The best take out asian food in the city!  Bar none!
